---
import PageLayout from "@layouts/PageLayout.astro";
import { pillars } from "@content/pillars";
---

<PageLayout
  title="About"
  description="GovCompass is a free political education project making South Africa's governance, economy, safety, and human development legible to ordinary citizens."
>
  <h1 class="font-heading text-3xl font-bold text-text-primary mb-6">
    About GovCompass
  </h1>

  <div class="space-y-6 text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
    <p>
      GovCompass is a free political education project for South Africa. It
      started with a simple question: why is it so hard for an engaged citizen
      to understand how the country actually works? Not the party politics —
      the systems underneath. How money flows from Treasury to your town. Why
      the police solve so few cases. What drives economic growth and what
      blocks it. Why health and education outcomes lag behind what our spending
      should deliver.
    </p>

    <p>
      The result is a comprehensive series of over 70 articles spanning five
      interconnected topics — each mapping a critical dimension of how South
      Africa functions and where it fails.
    </p>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-3 my-2">
      {pillars.map((p) => (
        <a
          href={`/pillars/${p.slug}`}
          class="flex items-start gap-3 p-4 border border-gray-200 rounded-lg hover:border-gray-300 transition-colors group"
        >
          <span
            class="inline-block w-3 h-3 rounded-full mt-1 shrink-0"
            style={`background-color: ${p.color}`}
          ></span>
          <div>
            <span class="font-heading text-sm font-bold text-text-primary group-hover:text-compass-green transition-colors">
              {p.title}
            </span>
            <span class="block text-xs text-text-secondary mt-0.5">
              {p.description}
            </span>
          </div>
        </a>
      ))}
    </div>

    <p>
      Together these topics map the reinforcing cycle that connects governance
      quality to lived outcomes — and show where that cycle is broken. The
      site also includes a
      <a
        href="/government-functions"
        class="text-compass-green underline hover:text-compass-green-dark transition-colors"
      >State Functions</a> reference mapping every functional area across the
      three spheres of government, and a
      <a
        href="/real-steps-to-reform"
        class="text-compass-green underline hover:text-compass-green-dark transition-colors"
      >Reform Programme</a> consolidating over 80 concrete reforms into a
      sequenced, phased 10-year plan.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold text-text-primary pt-4">
      Who this is for
    </h2>

    <p>
      GovCompass is written for the "missing middle" — people who are
      educated, engaged, and frustrated, but were never taught how the system
      actually works. You vote, you pay tax, you read the news, but the gap
      between headline outrage and structural understanding remains wide. We
      aim to close that gap.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold text-text-primary pt-4">
      Editorial principles
    </h2>

    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
      <li>
        <strong class="text-text-primary">Non-partisan:</strong> GovCompass
        explains systems, not parties. We don't tell you who to vote for — we
        help you understand what you're voting for.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong class="text-text-primary">Evidence-based:</strong> Every claim
        is backed by publicly available data — from the Auditor-General and
        National Treasury to the UNDP Human Development Reports and the
        Harvard Growth Lab's economic complexity data.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong class="text-text-primary">Structurally focused:</strong> We
        diagnose systems, not symptoms. Each topic traces root causes, maps
        institutional design, and identifies where reforms have leverage.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong class="text-text-primary">Reform-oriented:</strong> We don't
        stop at diagnosis. The Reform Agenda series applies the RAARICLE™
        governance framework to propose concrete, sequenced institutional
        reforms — grounded in international evidence and costed where data
        permits.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong class="text-text-primary">Accessible:</strong> Written for
        smart people who aren't specialists. No jargon without explanation, no
        assumptions about prior knowledge.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong class="text-text-primary">Free:</strong> All content is free
        and always will be. No paywall, no premium tier, no ads.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold text-text-primary pt-4">
      Methodology
    </h2>

    <p>
      Each article follows a consistent methodology. We start with the
      constitutional and legislative framework — what the law says should
      happen. We then layer on institutional analysis — what actually happens
      and why. We use official data to quantify the gap between design and
      reality, draw on international comparators to show what is possible,
      and end with practical takeaways for citizens.
    </p>

    <p>
      Where we propose reforms — particularly across the Safety & Security,
      Economic Growth, and Reform Agenda series — we ground them in evidence
      from countries that have faced similar challenges. We sequence proposals
      by institutional prerequisites, estimate fiscal costs where data
      permits, and identify the political economy constraints that make
      implementation hard. The full reform programme is consolidated in our
      <a
        href="/real-steps-to-reform"
        class="text-compass-green underline hover:text-compass-green-dark transition-colors"
      >Real Steps to Reform</a> page.
    </p>

    <p>
      Sources are cited throughout and collected in our
      <a
        href="/data-sources"
        class="text-compass-green underline hover:text-compass-green-dark transition-colors"
      >Data Sources</a> page. We draw on official government publications,
      audited financial data, international development indices, academic
      research, and independent civil society analysis — never unnamed
      sources or speculation.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold text-text-primary pt-4">
      Contact
    </h2>

    <p>
      Questions, corrections, or suggestions? Reach out at
      <strong class="text-text-primary">hello@govcompass.co.za</strong>.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageLayout>
